Cooler than normal was the most western part of Europe, with in Ireland and the western part of the Iberian Peninsula around ten cold days (days with a maximumtemperature < 10th percentile).
<br><br>
<a href="../images/jun2019/Stateofclimate_Indices_tg10p_2019_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_TG10p_baselayers_overlay_2019-06-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/jun2019/Stateofclimate_Indices_tg10p_2019_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_TG10p_baselayers_overlay_2019-06-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<a href="../images/jun2019/Stateofclimate_Indices_tg10p_2019_month_nc__2019-06-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/jun2019/Stateofclimate_Indices_tg10p_2019_month_nc__2019-06-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
<br><br>
<em>Figure 4: TG10p: Days with TG < 10th percentile (cold days) in June 2019 (based on E-OBS)</em>
<br><br>
The first week of June heavy thunderstorms developed over the western part of Europe. Later in the month also heavy thunderstorms developed over southeastern Europe, locally resulting in one-day precipitation amounts of around 50 mm.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/jun2019/Stateofclimate_Indices_r10mm_2019_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_R10mm_baselayers_overlay_2019-06-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/jun2019/Stateofclimate_Indices_r10mm_2019_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_R10mm_baselayers_overlay_2019-06-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
