<h2>The weather in June 2019</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
Over most of Europe, the average temperature in June 2019 was higher than the 1981-2010 average for the month and it was particularly warm over parts of central and eastern Europe. Around the middle of the month temperature records were broken in eastern Europe. Then towards the end of the month (25-29 June), the western and central parts of the continent experienced a short but record-breaking heatwave, with daily average temperatures up to 10°C higher than normal (see event description). For the month as a whole, the only areas that were cooler than normal were western Iberia and parts of the British Isles. This distribution was due the main location of the upper trough over low pressure, from the British Isles towards western Iberia, and high pressure over the continent.
<br><br>
