<br><br>
<em>Figure 10: European land surface temperature: annual anomalies with the current year in green. The grey bands show the uncertainty in the averaged temperature (left). Daily anomalies with respect to the seasonal cycle until the end of June 2019 (right). (Based on E-OBS)</em>
<br><br>
<h3>Precipitation</h3>
Due to the main influence of high pressure over the continent, we can see in general dry conditions over southwestern, central and eastern Europe. Parts of western Europe could see some high precipitation days due to the eruption of heavy thunderstorms in the first week of June.
