<h3>Cloudiness and Radiation</h3>
<br><br>
Due to the strong high pressure area and corresponding significant subsidence, we can see a strong positive anomaly over radiation (negative anomaly in cloud cover) over much of the western- and central Europe. In an area from western Iberia into England a zone with negative anomalies in radiation can clearly been seen due to a lot of cloudy days corresponding with frontal systems which took a hold along the western edge of Europe.
